    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 268.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">McLane</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 10, 1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that copies of your dispatch
                    No. 28 of the 23d ultimo, containing a copy of a note addressed to you by Mr. de
                    Freycinet, with reference to the way in which the gift of France was received
                    upon its arrival at New York, have been communicated to the Secretary of the
                    Navy and the mayor of New York.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAS. D. PORTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
